(Cases called at 10:32 AM - 13CF230 and 15CF934)
Defendant Fue Yang appears in custody with Attorney Laurie Osberg.  Deputy District Attorney Peter J. Rindal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court notices that her husband has been an attorney on 13CF230 at some point and will not be able to proceed with the plea today due to the potential of a conflict of interest.  Branch 4 (Judge Theisen) has agreed to enter the plea today for Branch 5.  If probation is revoked, Judge Harless will recuse herself at that time and case will be reassigned to a new judge for sentence after revocation proceedings.  (Case recalled at 10:40 AM)  Judge Jon Theisen for Branch 5.  State outlines agreement for the Court.  Defendant advised of the elements and maximum possible penalties of the charges to which he will plead.  State files Amended Information in 13CF230.  Defendant pleads No Contest to 13CF230 Count 1: Possession of Methamphetamine (Repeater, Party to a Crime) and 15CF934 Count 1: Sex Offender - Fail to Update Information.  Defendant makes a statement.  State in compliance with victim notification requirements.  Court withholds sentence and orders 24 months of probation with the following conditions: 180 day jail (on 15CF934) with Huber, stayed pending further order of the Court.  Undergo and comply with any assessments, treatment, conditions recommended by Court.  Maintain absolute sobriety.  No contact with B.X. (co-defendant) or any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting.  Provide DNA sample and pay fee.  Court costs, to include warrant fee in 13CF230.  98 days sentence credit if revoked from probation.  Court has no objection to supervision being transferred to Minnesota.
